# Skill authoring (HeyEddi collection)

## Layout — installable triad

Each skill lives under `skills/<skill-name>/` — same structure as its standalone GitHub repo:

```
skills/<skill-name>/
├── SKILL.md
├── manifest.json
├── context/
│   ├── VOCABULARY.md
│   ├── ANTI_PATTERNS.md
│   └── EXAMPLES.md
├── reference/
└── scripts/
    ├── _skill_cli.py
    └── *.py / *.sh
```

**Do not** put distributable skills under `.cursor/skills/`. Consumers install via `npx skills add`.

## Distribution

- Subtree prefix: `skills/<name>/`
- Install locally: `./scripts/install-skills.sh <name> --project <app>`
- Publish: `./scripts/push-skill-subtree.sh <name> <remote>`
- Register remotes in `skills-registry.json`

## `.heyeddi/` in consumer projects

Skills read/write product and design context under `.heyeddi/` in the **app repo** (not this hub). See [docs/heyeddi-folder.md](../../docs/heyeddi-folder.md). `project-engineering` scaffolds `.heyeddi/README.md` via `scaffold_heyeddi`.

## Cloud

- `manifest.json` → `python3 scripts/cloud/register_tools.py .`
- Scripts use `_skill_cli.py`, `--project-root`, return text on failure

## Subagents

Skills that orchestrate multi-step work **delegate by default** via Cursor Task tool. Each skill may ship `reference/subagents.md`. Hub spec: [docs/subagent-delegation.md](../../docs/subagent-delegation.md). Cloud backend: same prompt shape as `delegate_to_skill` (Phase 7 roadmap).

